cs.LG, cs.CV, cs.AI, cs.NE, cs.GT. 

The paper discusses the training and generalization properties of generative adversarial networks (GANs), which are commonly used in computer vision (CV) and machine learning (ML) applications. Therefore, cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) are the most likely sub-categories. The paper also discusses the equilibrium in the discriminator/generator game, which falls under game theory (cs.GT) and neural networks (cs.NE). Finally, the paper proposes a new protocol for GAN training, which involves mixing different GAN models, and this falls under artificial intelligence (cs.AI).
